    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 17.88,
      "end": 20.84,
      "text": "Recorded by Lee Dunkleberg. Fort Worth, Texas.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 21.76,
      "end": 26.42,
      "text": "Dunkleberg.com. D-U-N-K-E-L-B-E-R-G.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 27.14,
      "end": 32.04,
      "text": "Asop's Fables. The Lion, the Bear, and the Fox.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 33.86,
      "end": 40.28,
      "text": "A Lion and a Bear were fighting for possession of a kid, which they both had seized at the same moment.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 41.1,
      "end": 48.06,
      "text": "The battle was long and fierce. And at length, both of them were exhausted.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 49.0,
      "end": 56.88,
      "text": "And lay upon the ground, severely wounded, and gasping for breath.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 58.88,
      "end": 64.44,
      "text": "A Fox had all the time been prowling around and watching the fight.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 65.64,
      "end": 75.28,
      "text": "And when he saw the combatants lying there too weak to move, he slipped in and seized the kid and ran off with it.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 76.28,
      "end": 80.58,
      "text": "They looked unhelplessly. And one said to the other,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 81.16,
      "end": 92.16,
      "text": "here we've been mauling each other all this while, and no one the better for it except the Fox.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 94.86,
      "end": 99.8,
      "text": "End of the Lion, the Bear, and the Fox.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
